At 05:42 PM 3/23/98 -0800, Richard wrote:
>This must seem really elementary to everyone, but inside of my program,
>how do i reset the value of the ir_data? I've been trying everything in
>the handyboard technical references but it gives me either a syntax error
>or  Cannot assign type <pointer to <function> >.

The cool thing is that you don't have to reset it; it resets itself
automatically.  When you call the function ir_data( 0 ), it returns the last
IR signal received, or zero if nothing has been received since the last time
you called it.

--Will
